        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 3:20PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 320 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Cabin Point, or near Claremont, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, penny size hail, and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible. Reduced visibility and minor flooding possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Claremont and Burrowsville around 325 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Taylors Corner,
Wayside, Brandon, Barnetts, Oak Hill Corner, Roaches Corner, New
Hope, and Barham.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
